The paper discusses a new logic representation that can potentially be used in beyond-Moore-law-chips, which suggests a focus on emerging technologies (cs.ET). The paper also deals with noise-based logic, which falls under the category of computer architecture and digital circuits (cs.AR). The modifications made to the logic representation aim to improve time complexity, which is a common concern in distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of quantum computing techniques, which could fall under the category of quantum physics and computation (cs.EM). Finally, the paper deals with the identification of a single product state, which could fall under the category of discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.LO).
